This paper is focused on natural language processing (NLP) techniques, specifically deep learning, to generate patent claims. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of pre-trained language models, which is a common technique in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of a span-pair classifier, which is a machine learning technique commonly used in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of a metric to measure the effectiveness of the patent claim generation, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a pre-trained Google BERT model, which is a common technique in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
